Description: Rim and upper body sherd of East Greek grey ware pottery dinos; dark grey fabric core sandwiched between beige margins, with mica and limestone inclusions; very worn dark grey slip and inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: Fram the same vase as 1888,0601.627. Which preserves what is probably part of the dedicator's name, ]krat[; the ending -os here is therefore most likely that of an ethnic.
Modern incised inscription on inside 'Diosk' indicates findspot.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.043)
